qas.question: Where is Valencia used instead of Catalan?
What are Catalan and Valencian the names for?
What affect does  different pronunciations in the two areas of Catalan speakers produce?

context: The endonym is pronounced /kə.təˈɫa/ in the Eastern Catalan <a2_0>dialects<a2_0/>, and /ka.taˈɫa/ in the Western dialects. In the <a0_0>Valencian Community<a0_0/>, the term valencià (/va.len.siˈa/) is frequently used instead. The names "Catalan" and "Valencian" are two names for <a1_0>the same language<a1_0/>. See also status of Valencian below.
